23/09/2004
BELGRADE, Serbia-Montenegro -- Serbian President Boris Tadic, leader of the Democratic Party (DS), and Prime Minister Vojislav Kostunica, leader of the Democratic Party of Serbia, are to meet on Thursday (23 September), according to state television. 
The two are expected to discuss the local elections in Serbia and the possible formation of a coalition at the local level. 
On Wednesday, Kostunica met with the deputy leader of the Serbian Radical Party (SRS), Tomislav Nikolic, to discuss a possible coalition. 
No details were disclosed. 
DS, meanwhile, urged Serbs to support DS candidates in the 3 October run-off vote, and offered co-operation to all parties but SRS and the Socialist Party of Serbia. 
(Danas - 23/09/04; Beta, B92 - 22/09/04)
